CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 25, 1960, pg. A8, reads: "Les Compes Entertain - Les Compes of the 1960 June graduating class of Westinghouse High School gave a gala affair at the Loendi Club. Above are shown the club members and their dates.  Left to right: Veronica Gloster and Charlie Gallman, Tommy Jean Jefferson and Meredith Bell, Mary Louise Nicholas and Donald Smalley, Rosalia Harrison and Joseph Taylor, Janice Peyton and Billy Robertson [Roberson].  Back row: Belva Stewart and LeRoy Daniels, Jean Blackwell (president) and Bernard Palmer.  Winifred Williams and George Blackwell.  Others who attended were Melvin Foreston, Sara Smith, Sonny Dunn, Barbara Williams, Clyde Myers, Sondra Woody, Earl Rainey, Lillian Oliver, Clarence Moore and Beverly Banks. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of members of Les Compes Club of Westinghouse High School, front row from left: Veronica Gloster, Charlie Gallman, Tommy Jean Jefferson, Meredith Bell, Mary Louise Nicholas, Donald Smalley, Rosalia Harrison, Joseph Taylor, Janice Peyton, William "Billy" Roberson; back row: Belva Stewart, LeRoy Daniels, Jean Blackwell, Bernard Palmer, Winifred Williams, George Blackwell, posed in Loendi Club, another version
